title: TSB offers £363 to customers who open new account with limited offer
text:
TSB offers £363 to customers who open new account with limited offer TSB offers £363 to customers who open new account with limited offer HIGH street bank TSB is offering new customers the chance to earn up to £363 a year through its current account with a deal launched today. PUBLISHED: 18:06, Fri, Oct 9, 2015 | UPDATED: 18:28, Fri, Oct 9, 2015 GETTY TSB customers can earn a bumper £363 with new offer 
The bank is paying people £125 to open a new 555 Classic Plus account through MoneySupermarket.com from October 9 until November 2. Customers need to switch through MoneySupermarket, or its site Moneysavingexpert.com, using the Current Account Switch Service, register a minimum of two active direct debits, and credit a minimum of £500 into their new account within 28 days of the switch being completed.The rest of the money can then be earned through a combination of high interest and cashback over 12 months that's offered by the competitive product. Five per cent of cashback is paid on the first £100 of contactless debit card payments made from the account each month, allowing up to £60 over a year to be banked. If the balance remains at £2,000 customers then get the full benefit of the five per cent in-credit interest, to bag £97.80 over a year. Related articles
